<br>
Me: Ye killed me scarab there, mate<br>
Him: No, I killed &quot;MY&quot; scarab<br>
Me: I was fightin him first ... he wasnt attacking you<br>
Him: Ah ok, thanks for tanking for me then bwahaha<br>
Me: You will not be fergotten, mate<br>
<br>
To which I think he said &quot;I know&quot;. A few minutes later, he said:<br>
<br>
Him: oh btw he had a scarab carapiece too /bow<br>
Me: good fer you ... I hope killin that one bug was worth ruinin yer reputation<br>
<br>
At some point in the exchange, he made some comment like why dont I go back to the carebear server that I came from - which really boggled me, as, by his reckoning, wouldnt <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> this</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> server be a &quot;carebear&quot; server as well?<br>
<br>
I eventually asked him if he was done yet, to which he, of course, challenged me to a duel.  I said no thanks, as I never duel (I mean, what does it really prove in this game - its not like Rocket Arena where we are all equal avatars .... er, well, those who dont cheat, anyway).  He said something like 'I didnt think so', and by the grace of Brell, that was the end of him.<br>
<br>
Yeah, the guy was a prick, and in RL may need a metaphorical slap upside the head, but I think he was trying to get under my skin more than anything, and/or perhaps had built up frustration from fighting in the newbie zone, and just flipped after my tell.  <br>
<br>
I really wanted to /report him, or at least lay into him in and OOC manner, but I kept telling myself to keep in character, and just deal with it.  I think I stayed in character as best I could, though I do need to think about some witty comebacks - at least an incident like this provides the perfect cauldron to stew up some new goodies.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, as I post this today, I am happy that I did what I did: he thinks we won a battle of macho because I didnt take him up on his duel, but I stayed in character, as hard as it was, and that was the most important thing for me to do.<br>
<br>
Oh, and I dont post names - I think that that is a dangerous trend.  If he crosses me enough, though, it should be know that I do keep all my screen shots .... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>-G<P><FONT size=-3>
